The paper discusses energy modeling for source code, which is a software engineering topic (cs.SE). It also involves identifying energy operations directly from the source code, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and augmented reality (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the complex run-time context and software stack, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper applies the approach to a class of applications based on a game-engine, which is related to multimedia (cs.MA).
